gameBattle.heatMapTheoryPseudoCode:
function chooseShot(board):
  candidates = allUnfiredCells(board)
  clusters = findUnsunkHitClusters(board)

  if clusters exist:
    focusCluster = highestPriorityCluster
    openCells = openCellsAround(focusCluster)

    if openCells is not empty:
      for each cell in candidates:
        base = number of valid ship placements crossing cell and satisfying the focused hits
        adjacency = bonus from neighbouring hit cells
        total = base + adjacency if cell is in openCells, otherwise 0
    else:
      total = 1 for cells around hit clusters, otherwise 0
  else:
    for each cell in candidates:
      base = number of valid ship placements crossing cell
      parity = bonus if cell belongs to the preferred checkerboard pattern
      center = bonus based on closeness to the board center
      total = base + parity + center

  choose the cell with the highest total
